{"id":"12217","name":"Hyphenate text","tagline":"Add soft (optional) hyphens to a text, with support for more than 70 languages","icon":"ios15 c4292093695 g61465","latest":"33590","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut adds by default soft (optional) hyphens to a text, following sets of hyphenation patterns originally from the TeX software.</p>\n<p>It can be useful where other things like <a href=\"https://caniuse.com/?search=CSS+Hyphenation\">CSS hyphenation</a> don't work (or until <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/CSS/hyphens#browser_compatibility\">multilanguage support</a> is more common).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The shortcut can receive <strong>plain text</strong> and it will be hyphenated following the patterns of the device language</li>\n<li>It can also receive a <strong>dictionary</strong> with the “text” to hyphenate, the code of the “language” whose patterns are to be used, and an optional “separator”, to be used instead of the default soft hyphen (U+00AD)</li>\n<li>The shortcut works as a <strong>demo</strong> when it doesn’t receive input, and as a <strong>function</strong> when it does</li>\n<li>The shortcut <strong>downloads</strong> from <a href=\"https://www.jsdelivr.com/package/npm/hyphen\">jsdelivr.net</a> the language patterns it needs when it needs them, but also <strong>caches</strong> an optimized version of them to speed up the execution, save bandwidth and minimize storage</li>\n<li>All the real work is done by <a href=\"https://github.com/ytiurin/hyphen\">Yevhen Tiurin’s JavaScript implementation of the TeX algorithm</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Examples</h3>\n<p>Example of use as a function with a dictionary (language: Latin, separator: \"~\"):<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.icloud.com/shortcuts/496dedb369cc4375a9b6aa764640ec44\">https://www.icloud.com/shortcuts/496dedb369cc4375a9b6aa764640ec44</a></p>\n<p>Example of use as a function with plain text (device language and soft hyphens*):<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.icloud.com/shortcuts/8f7816da33714fa793a9d79ff12b249b\">https://www.icloud.com/shortcuts/8f7816da33714fa793a9d79ff12b249b</a></p>\n<p>(*) Hyphenation can be checked by double tapping in the words of the output (fragments of the words will be selected, instead of whole words)</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - June 11, 2022, 8:59 p.m.</strong></p>"}